After three weeks Una could milk Red Cow or Kitty Shorthorn quite dry , without her wrists aching , and then she allowed Dan to look . 
But milking did not amuse him , and it was pleasanter for Una to be alone in the quiet pastures with quiet spoken Mrs Vincey . 
Once , in the middle of a milking , Kitty Shorthorn boxed Una's ear with her tail . 
'You old pig ! said Una , nearly crying , for a cow's tail can hurt . 
'Why didn't you tie it down , child ? said a voice behind her . 
She wore a yellow velvet cap and tan gauntlets , and carried a real hunting crop . 
Her cheeks were pale except for two pretty pink patches in the middle , and she talked with little gasps at the end of her sentences , as though she had been running . 
'You don't milk so badly , child , she said , and when she smiled her teeth showed small and even and pearly . 
