He had those fits sometimes . 
I wanted to know more about Monsieur Peringuey , and the emigre party was the very place to find out . 
It's neither here nor there , of course , but those French emigre parties they almost make you cry . 
It hurt me to take their money afterwards , indeed it did . 
And there I found out about Monsieur Peringuey . 
He was a proper rogue too ! None of 'em had a good word for him except the Marquise that kept the French boarding house on Fourth Street . 
I made out that his real name was the Count Talleyrand de Perigord a priest right enough , but sorely come down in the world . 
I'm telling you the talk in the washhouse . 
