'With one thing and another , and my being made a burgess of Rye , I never clapped eyes on him for the next twenty years . 
Oh , I had the news of his mighty doings the world over . 
They was the very same bold , cunning shifts and passes he'd worked with beforetimes off they Dutch sands , but , naturally , folk took more note of them . 
